Task: Draft an Antiâ€‘Mootness Preservation Memo.

Instructions:
1. Create a dated timeline showing when you filed (TRO/PI/request), when the opposing event was scheduled, and when the court acted.
2. Identify the points where delay made relief impossible and note each request you made for expedition or status.
3. Write a 2â€“3 paragraph argument invoking at least one antiâ€‘mootness doctrine (capable of repetition, voluntary cessation, collateral consequences, relationâ€‘back) and request an order preserving the status quo or expedited decision.
