âœ… Model Response
â€œPlaintiff filed a TRO on July 29 seeking to stay an August 15 administrative hearing. The Court deferred decision until after the hearing date passed. Defendants now argue the request is moot. But the issue is capable of repetition yet evading review: the same hearing process recurs on short notice and consistently terminates before judicial review is possible. Alternatively, the agencyâ€™s lastâ€‘minute pauses and restarts constitute voluntary cessation that does not moot the controversy. The Court should grant expedited relief and maintain the status quo, or clarify that the claim is not moot and proceed to the merits.â€

